# .private-info-blocklist.example — format reference for .private-info-blocklist
#
# Copy to .private-info-blocklist (gitignored) and add your own patterns.
# Each non-blank, non-comment line is a POSIX extended regex.
# Matched content triggers a scan-outbound.sh violation.
#
# Setup: cp .private-info-blocklist.example .private-info-blocklist
# Or let the installer create a symlink from a private repo.
# See docs/scan-outbound.md for full details.

# Hostname / machine name (POSIX word-boundary style)
# (^|[^[:alnum:]_])myhostname([^[:alnum:]_]|$)

# Corporate / org identifiers
# mycompany
# internal-domain\.example\.com

# Block unwanted commit message metadata
# Co-Authored-By

# API key variable names (match .env assignment lines)
# ^YOURSERVICE_API_KEY=

# Private local paths
# C:\\Users\\myname\\private
